# Civil Rights History Project — RAG layer environment variables
#
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development. Set the production
# values in the Netlify dashboard under Site settings → Environment
# variables (and/or the Supabase Edge Function secrets store, depending
# on where the chat function ultimately lives). Never commit a populated
# .env or .env.local — they are gitignored.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pinecone — vector retrieval
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Index settings (per 2026-05-25 provisioning):
#   - Name: civil-rights
#   - Dimension: 1024 (voyage-3)
#   - Metric: cosine
#   - Type: Serverless (Builder tier default)
#   - Cloud + region: aws-us-east-1
#
# CURRENT STATE: civil-rights index is co-mingled with worldthought
# in a single Pinecone project (shared host hash `odc9z70`) as a
# provisional shortcut. The intended end state is SEPARATE projects
# under the same Builder organization for least-privilege access.
# Migration path documented in rag/.env.local (gitignored).
PINECONE_API_KEY=
PINECONE_INDEX=civil-rights
# Pinecone serverless index host — find in the Pinecone console under
# the index's "Connect" tab. Current value:
#   https://civil-rights-odc9z70.svc.aped-4627-b74a.pinecone.io
PINECONE_HOST=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Voyage AI — embeddings + reranking
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# voyage-3 (1024-dim) is the default for document and query embedding.
# rerank-2 is the default for the second-stage reranker.
# Voyage API keys are issued at https://dash.voyageai.com/
VOYAGE_API_KEY=
VOYAGE_MODEL=voyage-3
VOYAGE_RERANK_MODEL=rerank-2

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Anthropic — auxiliary scripts (optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Not required for the RAG layer itself — the MCP server pattern shifts
# LLM cost to the client (Claude Desktop / Custom Connector users supply
# their own subscription). This key is used by the dual-scorer +
# citation-auditor pipeline at Metadata Generation System/processor/.
# Safe to leave blank for RAG-only work.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build / deploy
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
SITE_HOST=civil-rights-staging.netlify.app
URL=https://civil-rights-staging.netlify.app
